  "prompt": "What is the best way to clean house windows?",
  "response": "Here are some effective methods for cleaning house windows:\n\n1. Basic cleaning solution\n- Mix equal parts white vinegar and water\n- Or use a commercial window cleaner\n- Use a microfiber cloth or soft sponge\n\n2. Tools needed\n- Squeegee\n- Microfiber cloths\n- Soft, lint-free rags\n- Bucket\n- Cleaning solution\n\n3. Step-by-step process\n- Remove dust and cobwebs with a dry cloth\n- Apply cleaning solution with sponge or cloth\n- Use squeegee to remove solution from top to bottom\n- Wipe edges with a clean, dry cloth\n- Use horizontal strokes on one side, vertical on the other to easily spot streaks\n\n4. Additional tips\n- Clean on a cloudy day to prevent solution from drying too quickly\n- Use newspapers for a streak-free shine\n- For exterior windows, use a garden hose to pre-rinse\n- Consider using a extendable window cleaning tool for hard-to-reach areas\n\n5. Professional options\n- Hire window cleaning service for thorough cleaning\n- Use professional-grade cleaning equipment\n\nAlways test cleaning solutions on a small area first to ensure they don't damage your windows.",
